    <section>                                                                  <!--2-->
      <title>In Haven Everything is Fine</title>
      <abstract>
        Borders are becoming less relevant to many of us, in a world of rapidly developing networked communication. But some recent events remind us how much borders still matter: Panama Papers, the history's biggest data leak from the database of the offshore law firm Mossack Fonseca, that contains evidence that some of the world’s richest people have used national borders to shield chunks of their massive wealth from other countries’ taxing authority.
      </abstract>
      <table>
        <row type="head">
          <cell>Tax Evasion</cell>
          <cell>Tax Avoidance</cell>
        </row>
        <row type="cell">
          <cell>Evasion is an illegal practice where individuals, corporations or trusts dodge paying their true tax liability.</cell>
          <cell>Tax avoidances are a legal actions taken to lessen tax liability and maximize after-tax incomes.</cell>
        </row>
      </table>
