    <section>                                                                        <!--6-->
      <title>Global Offshore Wealth</title>
      <abstract>
        The total amount of global offshore wealth corresponds to $7,600 billion. This means that, according to "The Hidden Wealth of Nations" - a recent book by Gabriel Zucman, economist at the University of California, Berkeley -, tax evasion costs governments approximately $190 billion per year. Let's make this simple and clear: tax evasion means less money for schools and roads, more money for drug barons and worse.
