    <section>                                                                      <!--8-->
      <title>Financial Transparency</title>
      <abstract>
        There is still a complete lack of financial transparency in several tax havens around the world - and recently this has become a hot topic after the Panama Papers case. We need to create a unified global register of financial securities. This involves putting Central Depositories under public control.
      </abstract>
      <chapter>
        <title>OECD Standards</title>
        <paragraph>Since 2014, 97 jurisdictions have agreed to impose new disclosure requirements for bank accounts, trusts, and some other investments held by international customers. Of the nations the OECD asked to sign on, only a handful have declined: Bahrain (Middle East), Nauru, Vanuatu (both in Oceania) — and the United States.</paragraph>
      </chapter>
