      <title>The Future of Journalism</title>
      <subtitle>A New Direction for Investigative Reporting</subtitle>
      <abstract>
        The investigation requires a lot of time and is a type of reporting among the most expensive. Nevertheless some new online tools are gradually allowing reporters to uncover, distribute and display data in fastest and least expensive ways.
      </abstract>
      <chapter>
        <subtitle>The Outcomes</subtitle>
        <paragraph>
          <list type="ordered">
            <item>CROSS BORDER COOPERATION: new web platforms allow to connect journalists and reportes working in the same field and helping each other to get information from local registries and databases.</item>
            <item>DATA JOURNALISM: this ambit of journalism has made on the basis of the analysis of digitized data of different nature, making possible to tell stories that otherwise would be really difficult.</item>
            <item>ENCRYPTION AND ANONYMITY: there are new foundamental tools, that have become more widespread and easy to use, making it safer in some ways than ever before for sources to reach out to journalists across the globe.</item>
