    <section>                                                            <!--11-->
      <title>Printed Press is Withering</title>
      <subtitle>The Side Effects of the Digital Journalism</subtitle>
      <abstract>
        The spread of Internet and digital communication tools has had heavy implications on traditional journalism. Publishing a daily or weekly newspaper required to a lot of money and this were once mainly guaranteed by the advertising. But things have changed now.
      </abstract>
      <chapter>
        <title>Advertising Market Covered by the Press</title>
        <paragraph>In the last years the coverage of printed press in the advertising market has dropped to 11.4%, while Google had a €44.5 million income with ads in 2015. For publishers the only solution is to charge for web content through paywall. Meanwhile the Guardian, which has a great free web-site, has seen its sales fall losing €72,2 million.</paragraph>
      </chapter>
