      <title>A Brief History of Leaks</title>
      <chapter>
        <paragraph>
          <list type="unordered">
            <item>CABLEGATE - 1.7GB - WikiLeaks (2010): Classified cables that had been sent to the US State Department by 274 of its consulates, embassies, and diplomatic missions around the world.</item>
            <item>OFFSHORE LEAKS - 260GB - ICIJ (2013): Investigation based on a cache of 2.5 million secret records about the offshore assets of people from 170 countries and territories, obtained by ICIJ's director.</item>
            <item>LUXEMBURG LEAKS - 4GB - ICIJ (2014): Investigation based on confidential information about Luxembourg’s tax rulings set up by PwC from 2002 to 2010 to the benefits of its clients.</item>
            <item>SWISS LEAKS - 3.3GB - ICIJ (2015): Investigation on a giant tax evasion scheme allegedly operated with the knowledge and encouragement of the British multinational bank HSBC via its Swiss subsidiary.</item>
            <item>PANAMA PAPARS - 2.6TB - ICIJ (2016): The Papers are 11.5 million leaked documents that detail financial and attorney–client information for more than 214,488 offshore entities. The leaked documents were created by Panamanian law firm and corporate service provider Mossack Fonseca; some date back to the 1970s.</item>
          </list>
        </paragraph>
