    <section>                                                                  <!--17-->
      <title>Reactions of Countries Implicated in Panama Papers</title>
      <abstract>
        This is only a small part of the list of the reactions to Panama Papers - related to offshore tax havens -, and response's of many countries and other official bodies relating to the mass leak of legal documents.
      </abstract>
      <chapter>
        <paragraph>The revelations have been discredited or censured.</paragraph>
        <paragraph>
          <list type="unordered">
            <item>RUSSIA: Putin denounces Panama Papers as a US plot to destabilize Russia. “The easiest way to do so is to induce some mistrust to authorities within the society” Putin said, adding that the creators of the leak aimed at the unity of the multiethnic Russian people.</item>
            <item>CHINA: All mentions of Panama Papers were banned from Chinese websites and newspapers.</item>
          </list>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph>The leak have led to internal investigations.</paragraph>
        <paragraph>
          <list type="unordered">
            <item>ICELAND: A petition of 16,000 signatures and the power of newspapers have allowed the resignations of the First Minister Gunnlaugsson.</item>
            <item>FRANCE: French president Francois Hollande welcomed the revelation of Panama papers: “I can assure you that investigations will be conducted”.</item>
            <item>ITALY: The italian IRS will investigate the 800 Italians that appeared in tax havens files.</item>
          </list>
        </paragraph>
      </chapter>
      <chapter>
        <title>But... Where Are the Americans at?</title>
        <paragraph>Unfortunately the leaker has made the dreadful mistake of turning to the western corporate media to publicise the results. In consequence the first major story, published by the Guardian is all about Vladimir Putin. But why focus on Russia?</paragraph>
      </chapter>
      <quote>
        <author>Craig Murray</author>
        <role>Author and human rights activist</role>
        <text>Russian wealth is only a tiny minority of the money hidden away with the aid of Mossack Fonseca. In fact, it soon becomes obvious that the selective reporting is going to stink.</text>
